<section id="sec.itk_inst">
<title id="title.itk_inst">Insight Toolkit (<acronym>ITK</acronym>)</title>

<section>
<title>Introduction</title>

<para>The <ulink url="http://www.itk.org">Insight Toolkit</ulink>
(<acronym>ITK</acronym>) is an open-source software library for
performing segmentation and registration.  When the
<acronym>ITK</acronym> toolkit is present, and &sr; is appropriately
configured, <acronym>ITK</acronym> filters can be encapsulated in &sr;
modules for use in &sr; networks.  By default, &sr; encapsulates a
subset of <acronym>ITK</acronym> filters.</para>

<para>&sr; encapsulates <acronym>ITK</acronym> filters using
<acronym>XML</acronym>-based filter description files.  An
<acronym>XSLT</acronym> processor generates code for &sr; modules from
the <acronym>XML</acronym> descriptions and <acronym>XSL</acronym>
stylesheets.  Users may encapsulate additional filters by writing
<acronym>XML</acronym> descriptions of them.  See the <ulink
url="../../User/Guide/usersguide/srug8.html">&sr; Users Guide</ulink>
for more information.</para>

<para>&sr;'s <acronym>ITK</acronym> support depends on the
presence of Java JDK 1.2.2 or later.</para>

<note>
<para>The <acronym>RPM</acronym> distribution of &sr; 
<emphasis>includes</emphasis> support for <acronym>ITK</acronym>.  The
<acronym>RPM</acronym> distribution installs Insight libraries in
/usr/local/lib/InsightTookit.  The instructions  in sections
<citetitle><link endterm="sec.title.obitk"
linkend="sec.obitk"/></citetitle>, <citetitle><link
endterm="sec.title.cmake" linkend="sec.cmake"/></citetitle>, and <citetitle><link
endterm="sec.title.itk_configsr" linkend="sec.itk_configsr"/></citetitle>
apply only
to source code installation of &sr;.</para>
</note>

</section>

<section id="sec.obitk">
<title id="sec.title.obitk">Obtaining <acronym>ITK</acronym></title>

<para>The Insight toolkit must be installed before building &sr;.  The
Insight toolkit and its installation instructions are available on the
<ulink url="http://www.itk.org"><acronym>ITK</acronym> web
site</ulink>.  &sr; supports <acronym>ITK</acronym> version 1.4.
<acronym>ITK</acronym> installation requires CMake, an open-source,
cross-platform build tool.  CMake can be obtained from the <ulink
url="http://www.cmake.org">CMake web site</ulink>.</para>

<note>
<para>&sr;'s Insight package must also be downloaded to add support
for ITK in &sr;.  See <link endterm="sec.title.sources"
linkend="sec.sources"/>.</para>
</note>

</section>

<section id="sec.cmake">
<title id="sec.title.cmake">CMake Special Instructions</title>

<para>CMake is a program that generates Makefiles that build ITK.
CMake's configuration variables determine how ITK is built.  Command
<command>ccmake</command> is used to configure CMake's variables.  In
particular, the value of CMake variable
<varname>BUILD_SHARED_LIBS</varname> must be explicitly set.</para>

<para>On SGI and Linux, <varname>BUILD_SHARED_LIBS</varname> must be
set <userinput>ON</userinput>.  On OSX
<varname>BUILD_SHARED_LIBS</varname> must be set
<userinput>OFF</userinput></para>

</section>

<section id="sec.itk_configsr">
<title id="sec.title.itk_configsr">Configuring &sr;</title>

<para>The configure options below add support for Insight
in &sr;.  Include these options in the &sr;
<command>configure</command> command (see <citetitle
pubwork="section"><xref linkend="sec.build-sr"
endterm="title.build-sr"/></citetitle>).
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--with-insight=<replaceable>path-to-insight-libs</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem>
<para>Specifies the directory containing the <acronym>ITK</acronym>
libraries.  The
<citetitle>ITK Software Guide</citetitle> refers to this directory as
ITK_BINARY_DIR.  The <acronym>ITK</acronym> library (or binary)
directory is commonly
<filename>/usr/local/lib/InsightToolkit</filename>.  The directory
will contain file <filename>ITKConfig.cmake</filename>.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>
<para>Here is an example <command>configure</command> command:
<literallayout class="monospaced">
../src/configure \
  --with-thirdparty=/usr/local/&sr;/Thirdparty/1.10.0/Irix/CC-32bit \
  --enable-package="Insight BioPSE" \
  --with-insight=/usr/local/lib/InsightToolkit
</literallayout>
</para>

</section>

